---
# ─── IDENTITY ───────────────────────────────────────────────
book: "{{book_slug}}"                    # e.g., "condensed-brain"
chapter: {{chapter_number}}              # integer, 1-indexed
title: "{{chapter_title}}"               # from outline.md
slug: "{{chapter_slug}}"                 # kebab-case, stable

# ─── LIFECYCLE ──────────────────────────────────────────────
status: "drafting"                       # drafting | in_review | edited | locked
stage: 9                                 # 1..11 in the GHOSTWRITR pipeline
generated_by:
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-5"             # drafting model (Sonnet for cost)
  agent: "quill"
  timestamp: "{{iso8601_now}}"
  run_id: "{{workflow_run_id}}"
revision: 1

# ─── VOICE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
voice_profile: "voice-profile.md"        # book-scoped artifact, relative path
voice_critic_family: "openai"            # MUST differ from author family (claude)

# ─── WORD BUDGET ────────────────────────────────────────────
target_words: {{target_words}}           # from outline; typical 2500-4500
actual_words: 0                          # filled by agent on write; validator reconciles
tolerance_pct: 10                        # ±10% acceptable before gate fails

# ─── CONSUMPTION CONTRACT (inputs this draft requires) ──────
sources:
  book_scoped:
    - path: "book-brief.md"              # stage 1
      required: true
    - path: "viability-report.md"        # stage 2 — must be PASSED
      required: true
      min_score: 3.5
    - path: "outline.md"                 # stage 3
      required: true
    - path: "base-story.md"              # stage 5
      required: true
  chapter_scoped:
    - path: "chapters/{{chapter_slug}}/bones.md"           # stage 4 paragraph topics
      required: true
    - path: "chapters/{{chapter_slug}}/research.md"        # stage 6
      required: true
      min_verified_claims: 3
    - path: "chapters/{{chapter_slug}}/external-stories.md" # stage 7
      required: true
      min_stories: 1
    - path: "chapters/{{chapter_slug}}/personal-stories.md" # stage 8
      required: true
      min_stories: 1

# ─── ME-WE-TRUTH-YOU-WE SLOT MAP ────────────────────────────
# Each slot points at the artifact section(s) Quill should weave in.
# This is the load-bearing structure — do not reorder.
framework:
  me:
    target_words: {{me_words}}           # ~15% of chapter
    draws_from:
      - "personal-stories.md#opening-hook"
  we:
    target_words: {{we_words}}           # ~20%
    draws_from:
      - "external-stories.md"
      - "base-story.md#shared-premise"
  truth:
    target_words: {{truth_words}}        # ~35% — the teaching spine
    draws_from:
      - "research.md#verified-claims"
      - "outline.md#chapter-{{chapter_number}}-big-idea"
  you:
    target_words: {{you_words}}          # ~20% — reader-facing application
    draws_from:
      - "bones.md#application-paragraphs"
  we_close:
    target_words: {{we_close_words}}     # ~10% — shared resolution
    draws_from:
      - "personal-stories.md#closing-beat"

# ─── GATE STATE ─────────────────────────────────────────────
gate:
  state: "pending"                       # pending | passed | failed
  checks:
    word_count_within_tolerance: null
    all_sources_present: null
    framework_slots_filled: null
    voice_critic_score: null             # ≥ 3.5/5 from opposing-family critic
    no_unverified_claims: null           # every factual claim traces to research.md
  last_checked: null
  checked_by: null
---

<!-- agent:quill
  You are drafting Chapter {{chapter_number}}: "{{chapter_title}}".
  Read ALL files listed in `sources` before writing a single sentence.
  Follow the ME-WE-TRUTH-YOU-WE framework section order exactly.
  Respect each slot's target_words within ±15%.
  Cite research via inline anchors: [R:{claim_id}]. The editorial stage resolves them.
  Cite stories via: [PS:{story_id}] (personal) or [ES:{story_id}] (external).
  Do NOT invent facts. If a slot lacks source material, emit a TODO comment
  and fail the `all_sources_present` gate check rather than hallucinate.
  Chris's brain condenses — your job is to EXPAND. Prefer concrete examples,
  specific numbers, named moments. No abstract throat-clearing.
-->

# Chapter {{chapter_number}}: {{chapter_title}}

<!-- agent:quill section=me
  Open with a first-person moment. Lived, specific, sensory.
  Draw from personal-stories.md#opening-hook. Land the reader IN a scene
  before they know what the chapter is about. Target: {{me_words}} words.
-->
## ME — The moment it hit me

{{me_slot}}

<!-- agent:quill section=we
  Shift from "I" to "we." Show this is a shared human pattern, not just
  your story. Weave at least one external story (ES:) with the shared
  premise from base-story.md. Target: {{we_words}} words.
-->
## WE — You've been here too

{{we_slot}}

<!-- agent:quill section=truth
  The teaching spine. This is where the chapter earns its keep.
  Load-bearing claims MUST cite [R:claim_id] anchors from research.md.
  Unpack the chapter's big idea from outline.md. Use the bones.md
  paragraph topics as scaffolding but expand each beyond its seed.
  Target: {{truth_words}} words. This is the longest slot.
-->
## TRUTH — What's actually going on

{{truth_slot}}

<!-- agent:quill section=you
  Turn the teaching outward. Second person. Practical, applicable,
  specific to the reader's situation. Draw application paragraphs
  from bones.md#application-paragraphs. Target: {{you_words}} words.
-->
## YOU — What this means for you

{{you_slot}}

<!-- agent:quill section=we_close
  Close the loop. Return to "we." Echo the opening ME scene with new
  meaning. Draw from personal-stories.md#closing-beat. Leave the
  reader with one concrete next action or reframe.
  Target: {{we_close_words}} words.
-->
## WE — Where this leaves us

{{we_close_slot}}

